01:35.125 --> 01:37.575
Don't go.

01:37.750 --> 01:40.130
I have to go. I promised him.

01:41.667 --> 01:44.077
Now promise me
you'll look after yourself.

01:44.208 --> 01:45.668
Yeah.

01:46.500 --> 01:48.540
I'm going hunting. I love you.

01:55.375 --> 01:57.455
I love you too.

02:11.750 --> 02:13.830
- Go.
- I don't wanna go.

02:18.000 --> 02:21.380
- Hurry up.
- Nice to see you too, mate.

02:21.500 --> 02:23.960
Amazing news, by the way.
Congratulations.

02:24.125 --> 02:27.915
Thanks, Marcus. It's pretty crazy, eh?

02:28.000 --> 02:30.080
Pretty crazy.

02:34.000 --> 02:35.210
- You okay?
- Mmm.

02:35.375 --> 02:37.375
- Will you be alright?
- Well, yeah.

02:37.500 --> 02:38.540
- Sure?
- Yep.

02:38.625 --> 02:39.625
Yeah.

02:49.708 --> 02:51.828
So I guess you finally had sex
with a woman.

02:51.917 --> 02:55.377
Yes, yes, and... and she was...
she was awake.

02:55.500 --> 02:58.250
- Yeah.
- That's a first.

02:58.333 --> 03:02.543
I know. I'm sorry. I know you always
wanted to be the one I got pregnant.

03:02.625 --> 03:07.245
Well, you might wanna double-check the
child doesn't come out looking like me.

03:07.333 --> 03:11.133
So how you been?
All this baby shit. It must be mad.

03:11.208 --> 03:15.418
Yeah, it is, man. It's insane.
It's fucking surreal.

03:15.500 --> 03:17.790
I'll actually forget
that she's pregnant.

03:17.917 --> 03:19.747
It freaks me out every time I remember.

03:19.833 --> 03:22.133
- It's insane.
- Oh, my God, man, I bet.

03:22.292 --> 03:25.042
- Yeah, yeah.
- Rather you than me, my friend.

03:25.167 --> 03:28.997
But, you know... I am pleased for you.

03:30.208 --> 03:32.918
Thanks, man. It's good to see you.

03:35.250 --> 03:37.040
You too, man. You too.

04:00.667 --> 04:03.707
- Bloody hell, man.
- Amazing, right?

04:03.833 --> 04:04.883
Yeah.

04:05.000 --> 04:08.210
The old man used to bring me here
hunting when I was a kid.

04:09.458 --> 04:11.538
Gunn's Wood.

04:12.250 --> 04:14.750
Reckon you can take down a deer?

04:14.833 --> 04:18.253
No. Probably not, no.

04:18.333 --> 04:20.463
Not everyone can do it.

04:21.541 --> 04:24.462
The trick is you have to switch off
your emotions, let instinct kick in.

04:24.583 --> 04:26.963
It's never seemed very fair to me, man,
shooting a deer.

04:27.125 --> 04:30.875
Well, life's not fair, Vaughn.
We learned that at school.

04:32.792 --> 04:35.752
Yeah, but we were 12, weren't we?

04:36.792 --> 04:39.332
This is it, Vaughny-boy,
the last few days of your freedom.

04:39.417 --> 04:43.127
- You have to enjoy it, man.
- I'm sorry. I know. It'll be fun.

05:23.500 --> 05:25.330
- Hi.
- Hi. I'm Freya.

05:25.417 --> 05:28.127
Marcus Trenton and Vaughn Carter?
Three nights?

05:28.208 --> 05:30.668
- That's right, yes.
- Yep.

05:30.750 --> 05:33.920
Addresses and phone numbers
in the book, please.

05:34.042 --> 05:35.082
Hey, wee man.

05:38.875 --> 05:41.195
It's quiet enough, isn't it?
Must all kick off around ten.

05:57.542 --> 06:02.252
So this is where they all hide.
Get a drink. I'm going for a slash.

06:09.625 --> 06:13.035
- How are you?
- Not bad. How you doing?

06:13.208 --> 06:16.828
I'm good. I, uh...
I hear that you're stalking.

06:16.917 --> 06:19.377
- Stalking?
- Aye, well, hunting.

06:19.500 --> 06:22.710
Oh, yeah, yeah. Yeah, we are, yeah.
It's not really my thing.

06:22.875 --> 06:27.625
It's my friend's gig, really.
He gave me a gun, got me a license.

06:27.708 --> 06:31.038
- Well, you know how to handle a gun?
- Yeah, yeah.

06:31.167 --> 06:34.747
I did a bit of shooting on a range
when I was at school, so yeah.

06:34.833 --> 06:37.883
Yeah, we haven't had so many folks
stalking this last season.

06:37.958 --> 06:41.328
There's a massive country club
opened 50 miles off.

06:41.458 --> 06:43.378
It drained a lot of our trade.

06:43.500 --> 06:46.460
I think my friend's made a point
of avoiding that place, so don't worry.

06:46.542 --> 06:49.902
Aye? Oh, good for him. I'm Logan, by the way.
- Vaughn. Nice to meet you. - And you.

06:51.708 --> 06:54.458
Oh, Marcus. This is Logan.

06:54.583 --> 06:56.793
Hey. Good to meet you.

06:56.917 --> 07:00.577
I hear that you lads might need
a ghillie out there with you tomorrow.

07:00.667 --> 07:02.077
Oh, no. We'll be stalking alone.

07:02.250 --> 07:05.170
It's all cleared with Lord Griffin.
My father knew him, so...

07:05.333 --> 07:08.883
Two pints of IPA, please,
two Laphroaigs and...

07:08.958 --> 07:12.038
- Can I get you a drink, Logan?
- Oh, no. I'm alright, thanks.

07:14.542 --> 07:18.752
You, uh... Well, you boys have
a good day's hunting out there, eh?

07:18.833 --> 07:20.543
We will.

07:26.167 --> 07:28.917
What? He'd have rattled on for hours.

07:30.667 --> 07:33.457
What did you say? What did you say?

07:33.542 --> 07:36.882
- Shut the fuck up.
- Straight to his face, man.

07:36.958 --> 07:39.708
Oh, the memory's still etched
in my mind.

07:39.792 --> 07:41.962
Nobody tried that
with the field marshal. Nobody.

07:42.083 --> 07:44.963
Fucking deserved it. The way
he used to talk to you, it wound me up.

07:45.042 --> 07:46.542
Loyal to the end, Vaughny-boy.

07:46.625 --> 07:49.705
In that case, borderline insane,
but, you know...

07:50.417 --> 07:52.037
God, he could be a mean old bastard.

07:52.208 --> 07:54.078
Yeah. Yeah, he could.

07:55.042 --> 07:56.172
You miss him?

07:57.292 --> 08:01.292
No, man, no. It's been...
It's been three years, you know.

08:02.958 --> 08:05.038
Yeah, fuck him.

08:06.750 --> 08:10.130
Oh, my God. Kara, you can't say that.

08:18.375 --> 08:20.455
Any chance of a drink?

08:21.958 --> 08:25.168
- Yeah, definitely.
- Two double whisky and cokes.

08:25.250 --> 08:27.380
I'm Kara. This is Iona.

08:28.833 --> 08:31.383
- Do you wanna get that?
- I'll get these, yes.

08:32.250 --> 08:34.750
Uh, Marcus, Vaughn.

08:35.707 --> 08:37.378
You alright, mate?

08:38.875 --> 08:41.558
- What the fuck you playing at?
- Jesus Christ. Take it fucking easy.

08:41.582 --> 08:44.383
Take your hands off my friend, big man.

08:44.458 --> 08:46.958
I'll knock you on your arse,
you fucking flash prick.

08:47.042 --> 08:50.332
- Will you, now?
- Alright, Donald, that's enough.

08:56.750 --> 08:59.130
Sit down, son.

09:00.417 --> 09:02.957
Enjoy your night.

09:04.417 --> 09:06.997
- I had that covered, man.
- Yeah, sure you did.

09:10.667 --> 09:11.877
- Sorry.
- It's alright.

09:11.958 --> 09:15.828
Two double whiskeys and cokes
and two IPAs, please.

09:15.917 --> 09:17.707
Keep an eye on your friend, huh?

09:22.125 --> 09:24.875
You guys picked
the perfect weekend to be here.

09:24.958 --> 09:27.498
- Oh, yeah? Why?
- Alban Eiler.

09:27.583 --> 09:30.003
Alban... Alban, what?

09:32.333 --> 09:34.883
- Alban Eiler.
- Oh, right, Alban Eiler.

09:36.125 --> 09:38.575
It's this big festival thing
on Sunday night.

09:38.667 --> 09:41.997
- The weekend gets boozy as hell.
- Oh, cool.

09:45.750 --> 09:51.290
Whoa. Do yourself a favor.
Steer clear of that wee lassie.

09:52.833 --> 09:54.333
What if I don't?

09:54.458 --> 09:59.378
Just offering some friendly advice,
pal. It's your funeral.

10:09.208 --> 10:10.458
Fucking...

10:12.500 --> 10:13.540
Whoo!

10:13.625 --> 10:16.785
<i>♪ A star above the city
in the northern chill ♪</i>

10:16.917 --> 10:20.377
<i>♪ A baby being born to the overkill ♪</i>

10:20.875 --> 10:23.625
<i>♪ No say, no place to go ♪</i>

10:24.500 --> 10:27.170
<i>♪ A TV and a radio ♪</i>

10:27.250 --> 10:30.750
<i>♪ Ambition and love
wearing boxing gloves ♪</i>

10:30.833 --> 10:33.673
<i>♪ And singing hearts and flowers ♪</i>

10:34.917 --> 10:37.037
<i>♪ But somewhere in my heart ♪</i>

10:37.125 --> 10:41.205
<i>♪ There is a star that shines for you ♪</i>

10:42.208 --> 10:46.208
<i>♪ Silver splits the blue
Love... ♪</i>

10:52.083 --> 10:54.213
- More!
- More, more, more!

11:01.792 --> 11:03.882
Don't do anything I wouldn't do.

11:06.333 --> 11:08.923
- Kara, shall we?
- Come on, then.

11:09.042 --> 11:11.172
Enjoy your night.

11:16.792 --> 11:20.172
- Marcus seems wild.
- Yeah, he is.

11:20.333 --> 11:22.543
- How long have you known him?
- Marcus?

11:24.125 --> 11:26.205
15 years.

11:29.708 --> 11:33.958
Met him at boarding school.
He kind of took me under his wing.

11:34.125 --> 11:36.705
I haven't really been able
to get rid of him since.

11:36.833 --> 11:39.833
- You went to boarding school?
- Yeah.

11:39.958 --> 11:41.958
- You did?
- Yeah.

11:43.375 --> 11:45.375
Why did you go there?

11:45.500 --> 11:49.250
Parents went to work abroad when
I was 12, so they chucked me in there.

11:49.417 --> 11:52.127
- Wow. That's pretty harsh.
- Yeah.

11:54.208 --> 11:56.078
Yeah, it is harsh.

11:56.167 --> 11:57.497
Fuckers.

12:09.333 --> 12:13.423
I've got a fiancée, and she's pregnant.

12:23.250 --> 12:24.830
Iona.

12:26.375 --> 12:28.915
- I'm sorry. Listen, I should have...
- Listen, no.

12:29.000 --> 12:30.960
- I should have said. I should...
- Listen.

12:31.083 --> 12:33.753
I have had a fucking boring week.

12:37.292 --> 12:41.542
My mum owns the inn.
And I have the bar keys.

12:43.125 --> 12:45.245
Just come and have a drink with me.

12:46.958 --> 12:49.038
- Yeah?
- Of course.

12:50.792 --> 12:52.502
Okay.

12:58.125 --> 13:00.915
- So you grew up here?
- Yep.

13:04.542 --> 13:08.712
I should probably think about leaving
soon, though, before it's too late.

13:08.833 --> 13:11.253
I don't know.
I think it's quite cool. I like it.

13:11.333 --> 13:14.543
- Try living here.
- This is true.

13:16.458 --> 13:18.748
So, how are you feeling
about being a dad?

13:18.875 --> 13:20.955
I don't know.

13:22.833 --> 13:25.583
I mean, it's fucking terrifying. It's...

13:25.708 --> 13:27.958
Yeah, course it is.

13:30.208 --> 13:32.578
No, I think you'll be okay.

13:32.708 --> 13:34.378
I hope so.

13:35.417 --> 13:37.167
Cheers.

13:48.542 --> 13:50.132
Rise and shine.

13:50.250 --> 13:52.630
Come on, Vaughn. Get up!

13:52.750 --> 13:54.500
We're late.

13:54.583 --> 13:58.173
Morning. Come on, Vaughn.
Hop to it. We're late.

13:59.917 --> 14:01.997
Get up.

14:21.375 --> 14:24.535
Someone crept back
suspiciously late last night.

14:24.625 --> 14:27.955
Nothing fucking happened, man, okay?
So just shut up.

14:28.042 --> 14:31.422
Just... I'm just hungover.

14:31.500 --> 14:33.580
I mean, how come you're so fresh?

14:34.583 --> 14:36.963
Oh, you're not sniffing
that shit again, are you?

14:37.083 --> 14:40.173
I didn't smoke. I told you, smoking
gives you hangovers, not alcohol.

14:40.250 --> 14:42.000
Jesus, man,
I thought you quit that stuff.

14:42.125 --> 14:43.825
I'm on my holidays.

15:18.333 --> 15:20.833
Jesus Christ, mate. You look like shit.

15:21.708 --> 15:23.788
Can you just do me a favor
and just shoot me?

15:23.917 --> 15:26.667
Here. Take a shot of this.

15:31.500 --> 15:33.830
- Oh, fuck. I've forgotten the ammo.
- You're joking me.

15:34.000 --> 15:35.920
We're gonna have to go back
to the hotel, mate.

15:36.000 --> 15:38.380
- Can I not just use yours?
- No, you can't just use mine.

15:38.458 --> 15:40.998
You can't put .270 ammo
into a .243 rifle.

15:41.083 --> 15:44.833
- You'll blow your own head off.
- Okay, I don't care. I'll just...

15:44.917 --> 15:48.037
Use my .22.
And please don't fucking drop that.

17:19.166 --> 17:21.287
You take it, man. I'm not.

17:24.500 --> 17:26.540
It's your spot, your kill.

17:33.125 --> 17:35.535
Now, remember what I said.

17:35.625 --> 17:38.375
Just relax and let it happen.

17:45.208 --> 17:47.918
Do it now, Vaughn. Take the shot.

17:56.500 --> 17:58.580
Do it. Now, Vaughn.

18:18.250 --> 18:20.750
Vaughn. Vaughn, come back. Vaughn, no.

18:23.083 --> 18:24.753
Vaughn.

18:26.708 --> 18:28.288
Vaughn.

18:41.667 --> 18:43.377
Sammy!

18:44.958 --> 18:46.498
Sammy!

18:56.500 --> 18:59.040
Here. Here.

18:59.917 --> 19:02.377
Come on. Come on.

19:13.458 --> 19:15.538
Okay, okay.

19:20.875 --> 19:22.995
You fucking...

19:26.708 --> 19:27.998
Shit.

19:34.792 --> 19:36.502
Sorry.

19:37.792 --> 19:39.462
Sammy.

19:40.708 --> 19:42.788
Sammy. Sammy!

19:43.750 --> 19:45.830
Oh, my boy!

19:47.083 --> 19:48.713
Sammy.

19:49.458 --> 19:51.168
Sammy.

19:52.875 --> 19:54.955
Oh, my boy.

19:57.875 --> 20:01.165
Oh, my boy. Oh, Sammy. I didn't see him.
I didn't see him. I didn't see him.

20:27.833 --> 20:29.043
I didn't...

20:31.375 --> 20:34.785
I didn't see him. I didn't see him.

21:14.833 --> 21:16.923
Oh, my God.

22:10.542 --> 22:14.582
Okay, here we go. Here we go. Come here.

22:14.708 --> 22:17.168
There we go. There we go.

22:17.250 --> 22:21.420
Come on. There we go. There we go.
There we go. There we go.

22:27.708 --> 22:29.748
Run. Run.

22:29.875 --> 22:31.535
Run.

23:42.542 --> 23:45.582
Marcus. Marcus.
What are you doing? Marcus.

23:48.125 --> 23:51.415
Marcus. Marcus. Marcus.
What are you doing?

23:51.542 --> 23:54.172
We have to be seen hunting
somewhere else.

23:54.250 --> 23:57.250
- What? We're just gonna report it.
- You shot a child.

23:59.208 --> 24:00.748
It was... It was an accident.

24:00.833 --> 24:02.583
- With my gun.
- It was a fucking accident.

24:02.667 --> 24:04.327
It's illegal for you to even use my gun.

24:04.458 --> 24:06.208
I don't care.
We just go to the police...

24:06.333 --> 24:07.923
- Go to the police?
- We explain.

24:08.000 --> 24:11.000
Stinking of whisky?
It'll be considered murder.

24:13.875 --> 24:17.165
Can you handle prison, mate?
Because I don't think I can.

24:17.292 --> 24:19.292
Jesus, fuck, man.
Jesus fucking Christ.

24:19.458 --> 24:22.668
- Fucking Anna, man. Fuck.
- Exactly, Vaughn. Exactly.

24:22.792 --> 24:24.882
You could be in for years.

24:26.667 --> 24:30.457
And I shot that man from over
a hundred yards away. I'm fucked too.

24:31.542 --> 24:34.752
Because I was protecting you, Vaughn.
Protecting you.

24:45.958 --> 24:49.038
They were in a tent.
They were probably tourists.

24:49.125 --> 24:51.745
And we are in the middle
of fucking nowhere.

24:51.833 --> 24:53.833
In hundreds of miles of forest.

24:56.042 --> 24:59.462
If we bury the bodies, it could be days,
weeks, months until they're found.

24:59.542 --> 25:02.922
I'm not fucking burying people.
Listen to what you're saying.

25:03.042 --> 25:06.832
We go back to that town and we come
back here tonight and we bury them.

25:07.583 --> 25:10.003
No, man.
Look, listen to yourself, Marcus.

25:10.083 --> 25:13.833
- We're not burying people.
- The alternatives are unthinkable.

25:16.417 --> 25:17.917
- Vaughn...
- Just shut up. Shut up.

25:18.083 --> 25:20.883
- You have to trust me.
- I... Shut up.

25:25.792 --> 25:27.882
I'm getting us out of this, mate.

25:29.333 --> 25:32.883
I'm doing this for both our sakes.
You just have to trust me.

25:35.125 --> 25:37.205
I can't do this, man.

25:38.375 --> 25:41.125
You have no choice.
You have no choice, Vaughn.

26:31.458 --> 26:34.328
We need to be seen up here.
Further north.

26:36.542 --> 26:38.582
There has to be something.

27:06.458 --> 27:08.078
Hi.

27:09.375 --> 27:12.665
Oh, it's a cold one. How are you?

27:12.750 --> 27:16.750
Culcarran's south.
What are you doing up here?

27:16.875 --> 27:19.245
We've been hunting Drumrain
all afternoon.

27:19.333 --> 27:24.003
Aye, Logan told me about you.
There's no other stalkers out.

27:29.333 --> 27:31.423
Be still.

27:40.000 --> 27:42.670
- How much for the fuel?
- Call it 20.

27:44.708 --> 27:47.128
Thank you. Have a nice day.

27:51.667 --> 27:53.377
Aye.

28:10.333 --> 28:12.003
You okay?

28:17.292 --> 28:19.712
Nothing happened out there, okay?

28:32.250 --> 28:35.750
Yeah, we could... Okay.
We could do that next... next week.

28:35.833 --> 28:38.133
Oh, okay. Got to go.

28:38.250 --> 28:40.630
- How did you get on?
- Oh, a total washout.

28:40.708 --> 28:46.458
Oh. Well, no chefs tonight.
But there's bar food at the Stag's.

28:46.542 --> 28:49.172
Or there's the restaurant there.
It's pricey, mind.

28:49.333 --> 28:52.173
- Thanks.
- Alright. Thank you so much.

28:52.292 --> 28:54.542
- Thank you.
- Night.

29:07.333 --> 29:09.383
We need to eat.

29:10.875 --> 29:14.245
And we need to get out there.
It won't look right if we don't.

29:34.750 --> 29:38.630
Hey. Fancy some more drinks tonight?

29:38.708 --> 29:41.078
- Not tonight.
- Maybe later?

29:41.208 --> 29:43.078
Tomorrow.
Let's go, Vaughn. I'm starving.

29:43.208 --> 29:46.538
- You okay?
- Yeah, just a bit hungover.

29:58.583 --> 30:02.133
- Uh, where is the restaurant?
- Just round to the left.

30:02.292 --> 30:04.382
Thank you.

30:14.667 --> 30:16.077
Evening.

30:16.167 --> 30:18.577
Join us if you like.

30:21.000 --> 30:23.080
Yeah, sure. Why not?

30:24.042 --> 30:26.672
This is... This is Al.
He's a cousin of mine.

30:26.792 --> 30:29.292
- Al, this is Marcus and Vaughn.
- Pleased to meet you.

30:29.375 --> 30:31.285
- Nice to meet you.
- Have a seat.

30:31.375 --> 30:32.995
Please.

30:35.708 --> 30:38.538
Successful day's stalking?

30:38.625 --> 30:40.535
Uh, no. A total washout.

30:40.625 --> 30:43.625
Oh. Well, let's see
if we can't improve things.

30:43.750 --> 30:46.500
I, uh, well, I...
I recommend the venison.

30:46.583 --> 30:48.293
Huh?

30:49.292 --> 30:52.002
- Yeah.
- Good. Peter, two more venison.

30:52.833 --> 30:55.673
- Some wine?
- Please.

31:00.375 --> 31:01.995
You look a bit rough. Are you alright?

31:02.125 --> 31:04.995
Yeah, yeah. Just had far too much
last night. Stupid.

31:05.083 --> 31:06.463
Don't feel great.

31:06.542 --> 31:09.042
That's really no state
to have gone hunting in.

31:09.958 --> 31:12.958
- Isn't that right, Alastair?
- Shocking behavior.

31:13.042 --> 31:15.882
Aye,
you wouldnae catch us doing that.

31:20.292 --> 31:23.212
- As long as you had a good time.
- Yeah.

31:24.083 --> 31:26.293
So where did you lads stalk?

31:27.917 --> 31:31.207
Drumrain. It's beautiful up there,
really beautiful.

31:31.292 --> 31:36.672
The woods are right enough.
But not the village. Not any more.

31:37.542 --> 31:39.422
Yeah, what's happening with that place?

31:39.500 --> 31:43.750
It's turning into a ghost town.
It's just dying, slowly, over time.

31:43.833 --> 31:47.793
These kind of villages, they, well,
they survive on a knife's edge.

31:48.458 --> 31:51.288
I can imagine it's quite rough
up here this time of year.

31:51.458 --> 31:54.958
Aye. And brutal not so long ago.

31:55.042 --> 31:57.922
There's always a risk
of things sliding back that way.

31:58.000 --> 32:01.000
Aye, it pretty well comes down
on the individual folk

32:01.083 --> 32:02.503
to maintain the order of things.

32:02.958 --> 32:06.878
Logan and his father before him,
they held this place together.

